# Fix Login Bug + Add PDF Calendar Upload for Holidays

## Problem 1: Login Not Recognizing Credentials
The [signup](file:///c:/web%20development%20projects/BUNKSMART/src/context/AuthContext.js#19-24) function stores email/password as-is, while [login](file:///c:/web%20development%20projects/BUNKSMART/src/context/AuthContext.js#25-35) compares them with strict `===`. Any difference in case or accidental whitespace causes login failure. Fix: normalize email (lowercase + trim) on both signup and login, and trim password.

## Problem 2: Manual Holiday Entry
The onboarding step 3 requires adding each holiday date manually. Fix: add a PDF upload option that extracts dates from an uploaded academic calendar using `pdfjs-dist`.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Auth Context

#### [MODIFY] [AuthContext.js](file:///c:/web%20development%20projects/BUNKSMART/src/context/AuthContext.js)

- In [signup](file:///c:/web%20development%20projects/BUNKSMART/src/context/AuthContext.js#19-24): normalize email with `.trim().toLowerCase()`, trim password
- In [login](file:///c:/web%20development%20projects/BUNKSMART/src/context/AuthContext.js#25-35): normalize email with `.trim().toLowerCase()`, trim password before comparing
- This ensures credentials always match regardless of case or trailing whitespace

---

### PDF Holiday Extraction Utility

#### [NEW] [pdfHolidayExtractor.js](file:///c:/web%20development%20projects/BUNKSMART/src/utils/pdfHolidayExtractor.js)

- Uses `pdfjs-dist` to parse uploaded PDF files client-side
- Extracts text from all pages (focusing on bottom sections where holidays are listed)
- Uses regex patterns to find dates in common formats (e.g., "15 August 2025", "Aug 15, 2025", "2025-08-15", "15/08/2025", "15-08-2025")
- Returns array of date strings in YYYY-MM-DD format

---

### Onboarding Page

#### [MODIFY] [page.js](file:///c:/web%20development%20projects/BUNKSMART/src/app/onboarding/page.js)

